CADILLAC LYRIQ OWNER'S MANUAL

Welcome to your new Cadillac LYRIQ. This manual contains important information about your vehicle's features, controls, and maintenance requirements. Please read this manual carefully to ensure the best performance and longevity of your vehicle.

The LYRIQ is Cadillac's first all-electric vehicle, built on GM's Ultium platform. This advanced technology provides exceptional range, performance, and charging capabilities.

CADILLAC LYRIQ OWNER'S MANUAL

Introduction
This manual provides essential information about features, controls, and maintenance of your Cadillac LYRIQ electric vehicle. Familiarizing yourself with this information will help you enjoy safe and efficient operation of your vehicle.

ocrText:
CHARGING YOUR LYRIQ

Your LYRIQ can be charged using various methods:
- Level 1 charging (120V household outlet)
- Level 2 charging (240V home or public station)
- DC Fast Charging (public fast charging stations)

To maximize battery life and performance, follow the recommended charging practices outlined in this section. The vehicle's charging port is located on the front driver's side fender.
rawText:
Charging Information

Charging Your Vehicle
The LYRIQ supports multiple charging options:
• Level 1 (120V) charging
• Level 2 (240V) charging
• DC Fast Charging

The charging port is located on the front driver's side fender. Press the charging port door to open.

ocrText:
INFOTAINMENT SYSTEM

The LYRIQ features a 33-inch advanced LED display that combines instrument cluster and infotainment functions. The system includes navigation, vehicle settings, climate controls, and entertainment options. 

You can operate the display using touch controls or voice commands. For optimal safety, some functions are disabled while the vehicle is in motion.

Infotainment System

Your LYRIQ features a curved 33-inch LED display with instrument cluster and infotainment functionality. The system provides access to:

• Vehicle Settings
• Climate Controls
• Media and Entertainment
• Phone Connectivity

SAFETY FEATURES

The LYRIQ is equipped with numerous safety features including:
- Forward Collision Alert
- Automatic Emergency Braking
- Lane Keep Assist with Lane Departure Warning
- Side Blind Zone Alert
- Rear Cross Traffic Alert
- Advanced Airbag System

These systems are designed to help prevent accidents and protect occupants in the event of a collision.

VEHICLE MAINTENANCE

Although electric vehicles require less maintenance than conventional vehicles, regular service is still essential. Follow the maintenance schedule in this manual to ensure optimal performance.

Regular maintenance items include:
- Tire rotation and pressure checks
- Brake system inspection
- Cabin air filter replacement
- Battery coolant system inspection
- Windshield wiper blade replacement
